1
00:01:37,959 --> 00:01:39,426
There's more over here!

2
00:01:39,527 --> 00:01:40,892
Bring another team!

3
00:01:42,764 --> 00:01:44,391
We'll need a lot more help!

4
00:01:45,934 --> 00:01:48,198
Are you okay? Is the baby all right?

5
00:01:49,237 --> 00:01:51,262
It's okay. You can stay with your dad.

6
00:01:51,339 --> 00:01:53,034
I'm not his father. He's alone.

7
00:01:53,108 --> 00:01:54,200
- Go with him.
- No, please.

8
00:01:54,275 --> 00:01:56,038
- You'll be okay.
- I want to be with you.

9
00:01:56,111 --> 00:01:57,100
Take him.

10
00:01:57,712 --> 00:01:59,509
I've got to find the mother.

11
00:01:59,881 --> 00:02:00,973
Now, go.

12
00:02:01,950 --> 00:02:02,917
Come with me.

13
00:02:02,984 --> 00:02:04,474
You'll be all right.

14
00:02:05,987 --> 00:02:08,547
Everyone, please stay where you are.

15
00:02:08,623 --> 00:02:10,523
We'll be with you in a minute.

16
00:02:34,849 --> 00:02:38,717
Get them out of there! It's going to blow!
Get them out!

17
00:02:39,487 --> 00:02:40,579
My boy!

18
00:02:43,424 --> 00:02:45,756
My boy! My little boy's in there!

19
00:02:54,736 --> 00:02:56,829
No, my baby's in there!

20
00:02:57,405 --> 00:02:59,032
I can't leave my boy!

21
00:02:59,374 --> 00:03:00,238
Stop!

22
00:03:00,341 --> 00:03:02,309
Stop, my baby's in there!

23
00:03:06,681 --> 00:03:07,705
My baby!

24
00:03:13,555 --> 00:03:14,544
Stop!

25
00:04:06,574 --> 00:04:07,563
Are you okay?

26
00:04:10,511 --> 00:04:11,808
Were you in the crash?

27
00:04:15,783 --> 00:04:18,081
No. I found this baby.

28
00:04:19,287 --> 00:04:20,845
I've got to find the mother.

29
00:04:21,456 --> 00:04:24,482
There's a woman over there.
She's looking for her baby.

30
00:04:28,830 --> 00:04:30,058
Right over there.

31
00:04:36,437 --> 00:04:37,768
Is this your baby?

32
00:04:42,143 --> 00:04:43,667
My sweet angel.

33
00:04:52,153 --> 00:04:54,053
I want to go to the nearest hotel.

34
00:04:55,290 --> 00:04:56,723
You've got to be kidding.

35
00:06:47,268 --> 00:06:48,758
You're not dead.

36
00:08:02,176 --> 00:08:06,306
An InterCity Air spokesperson indicates
an estimated 200 passengers were...

37
00:08:07,648 --> 00:08:10,344
Wire reports confirm a crash
of an InterCity Airjet...

38
00:08:10,418 --> 00:08:13,581
...in the northeast section of the county
at Route 7 and Lake.

39
00:09:31,432 --> 00:09:35,994
ALthough, remarkabLy enough,
peopLe maintained themseLves pretty weLL.

40
00:09:36,304 --> 00:09:40,798
PeopLe puLL together in a situation Like that
and the crew was very professionaL.

41
00:09:50,251 --> 00:09:51,309
Max.

42
00:09:51,986 --> 00:09:53,180
Max Klein.

43
00:09:53,254 --> 00:09:55,245
What the hell are you doing here?

44
00:09:55,823 --> 00:09:57,450
Just passing through.

45
00:09:57,558 --> 00:10:00,254
You bastard, you don't look any different.

46
00:10:00,361 --> 00:10:01,794
- Nice try.
- It's true.

47
00:10:01,862 --> 00:10:03,955
Look at you. I can't believe it!

48
00:10:04,632 --> 00:10:06,156
It's been 20 years.

49
00:10:10,004 --> 00:10:12,234
These are strawberry pancakes?

50
00:10:15,476 --> 00:10:16,465
I wanted...

51
00:10:17,211 --> 00:10:18,872
Do you have whole strawberries?

52
00:10:19,313 --> 00:10:20,439
I guess.

53
00:10:20,781 --> 00:10:22,271
Bring me a bowl, please.

54
00:10:24,518 --> 00:10:27,112
I don't remember you having
a thing for strawberries.

55
00:10:27,321 --> 00:10:30,154
How's Bill? Is he head
of the theater department yet?

56
00:10:30,391 --> 00:10:31,016
No.

57
00:10:31,258 --> 00:10:32,486
He was passed over.

58
00:10:32,893 --> 00:10:37,592
I'll make this quick. I can't stand going
through the list. My life's a disaster.

59
00:10:37,698 --> 00:10:38,960
No, it isn't.

60
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:41,100
- Yes, it is.
- Trust me.

61
00:10:41,736 --> 00:10:43,761
Your life isn't a disaster.

62
00:10:59,553 --> 00:11:03,011
I'm fat. I haven't written a play in years.
Timmy, my oldest...

63
00:11:03,090 --> 00:11:04,455
...has a learning disability.

64
00:11:04,525 --> 00:11:08,689
Thanks to therapy I love him for what
he is, not my fantasy of what he should be.

65
00:11:09,230 --> 00:11:12,927
The middle two, James and Sarah,
resent the extra attention Timmy got...

66
00:11:13,034 --> 00:11:15,229
...so they fuck up in school to punish us.

67
00:11:15,302 --> 00:11:19,136
They're working it out in a support group,
Siblings of the Learning Disabled.

68
00:11:19,473 --> 00:11:23,341
My youngest, Ellen, who was going to be
a great ballerina...

69
00:11:23,511 --> 00:11:26,969
...destroyed her ankle playing basketball
with her brothers.

70
00:11:27,515 --> 00:11:30,177
As for Bill, he's screwing a student.

71
00:11:34,088 --> 00:11:34,952
Pathetic.

72
00:11:35,022 --> 00:11:36,887
It's not even tragic.

73
00:11:38,025 --> 00:11:39,253
Have a strawberry?

74
00:11:39,326 --> 00:11:41,226
What good will that do?

75
00:11:41,662 --> 00:11:43,857
Forbidden fruit always does good.

76
00:11:52,106 --> 00:11:53,437
Forbidden fruit.

77
00:12:01,215 --> 00:12:02,910
I didn't come for that.

78
00:12:05,186 --> 00:12:06,346
It figures.

79
00:12:07,021 --> 00:12:08,648
You always were faithful.

80
00:12:09,256 --> 00:12:10,484
And you?

81
00:12:11,592 --> 00:12:13,287
Who'd have me?

82
00:12:14,128 --> 00:12:15,459
Wait a minute.

83
00:12:15,896 --> 00:12:18,057
Aren't you allergic to strawberries?

84
00:12:18,199 --> 00:12:21,066
Didn't you almost die when you were little
from eating a strawberry?

85
00:12:21,135 --> 00:12:22,602
I'm past all that.

86
00:12:23,771 --> 00:12:25,329
See? No reaction.

87
00:12:28,142 --> 00:12:29,700
No reaction at all.

88
00:12:55,002 --> 00:12:56,094
- That's him.
- What?

89
00:12:56,170 --> 00:13:00,436
Good morning. I'm Agent Parsons,
this is Agent Smith. We're with the FBI.

90
00:13:01,342 --> 00:13:04,505
You're registered as Mr. Max Klein...

91
00:13:04,678 --> 00:13:07,613
...1147 Varennes in San Francisco.
Is that correct?

92
00:13:08,816 --> 00:13:10,044
You got me.

93
00:13:10,284 --> 00:13:11,581
Can we come in?

94
00:13:18,659 --> 00:13:22,220
Were you on a flight from San Francisco
to Houston that made an emergency...

95
00:13:22,296 --> 00:13:23,456
Yes, I was.

96
00:13:23,531 --> 00:13:25,761
Took a hike from the scene?
Just up and left?

97
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:28,795
- What time is it?
- 10:00, Thursday morning.

98
00:13:29,003 --> 00:13:30,834
You've been missing almost a day.

99
00:13:30,905 --> 00:13:31,894
Missing?

100
00:13:32,039 --> 00:13:33,836
What are you doing here?

101
00:13:34,308 --> 00:13:37,744
You walked from the crash,
rented a car, drove to L. A...

102
00:13:38,045 --> 00:13:39,171
Why?

103
00:13:40,147 --> 00:13:42,081
They didn't need me anymore.

104
00:13:42,783 --> 00:13:44,341
Need you for what?

105
00:13:46,187 --> 00:13:47,677
Am I under arrest?

106
00:13:49,590 --> 00:13:51,319
You haven't done anything.

107
00:13:53,327 --> 00:13:54,385
Do you?

108
00:13:57,565 --> 00:13:59,032
Do you know this man?

109
00:14:12,279 --> 00:14:13,473
I'm Cindy Dickens...

110
00:14:13,547 --> 00:14:16,983
...of InterCity Air and I'm here
to help get you home.

111
00:14:17,384 --> 00:14:18,351
That's nice.

112
00:14:18,419 --> 00:14:21,013
No one's taken me home
since the first grade.

113
00:14:22,957 --> 00:14:26,051
I have tickets on AmTrak
to get you to San Francisco.

114
00:14:26,227 --> 00:14:28,388
Your train leaves in an hour.

115
00:14:28,529 --> 00:14:29,826
I want to fly.

116
00:14:29,930 --> 00:14:31,227
I'm sorry?

117
00:14:32,766 --> 00:14:35,462
You'll fly me back to San Francisco
for free...

118
00:14:35,936 --> 00:14:36,960
...right?

119
00:14:38,172 --> 00:14:39,230
Of course.

120
00:14:41,842 --> 00:14:45,141
But when I told your wife the good news,
she said that...

121
00:14:46,013 --> 00:14:49,005
...even before the unpleasant...

122
00:14:51,752 --> 00:14:52,810
Crash.

123
00:14:53,354 --> 00:14:54,514
Yes, right.

124
00:14:54,788 --> 00:14:56,881
Even before that...

125
00:14:57,992 --> 00:14:59,926
...you were afraid to fly.

126
00:15:00,394 --> 00:15:03,795
I'd love to fly home on your airline,
but I've got a request.

127
00:15:04,899 --> 00:15:06,025
Sir?

128
00:15:06,533 --> 00:15:08,524
I want to go first class.

129
00:15:11,272 --> 00:15:12,432
Super.

130
00:15:12,940 --> 00:15:14,669
With our compliments, sir.

131
00:15:22,182 --> 00:15:23,706
- Cockpit preparation?
- Completed.

132
00:15:23,784 --> 00:15:24,773
Light test?

133
00:15:24,852 --> 00:15:26,877
- Oxygen and interphone?
- Checked.

134
00:15:26,987 --> 00:15:28,249
- Yaw damper?
- On.

135
00:15:28,389 --> 00:15:29,378
Hydraulics?

136
00:15:29,456 --> 00:15:30,445
On.

137
00:15:32,526 --> 00:15:34,551
Sir, may I see your boarding pass?

138
00:15:36,630 --> 00:15:38,530
Your seat is right down the aisle.

139
00:15:45,039 --> 00:15:46,438
Is he on board?

140
00:15:54,281 --> 00:15:55,612
I just made it.

141
00:15:59,653 --> 00:16:01,177
I'm Bill Perlman.

142
00:16:05,192 --> 00:16:06,523
Going home, right?

143
00:16:06,627 --> 00:16:08,618
Glad to be going home, I bet.

144
00:16:09,063 --> 00:16:10,291
You're a shrink.

145
00:16:11,265 --> 00:16:12,493
That's right.

146
00:16:14,068 --> 00:16:17,265
I specialize in the treatment
of post-traumatic stress disorder.

147
00:16:19,740 --> 00:16:22,334
I wrote a book about it
and several airlines hired me...

148
00:16:22,409 --> 00:16:24,172
We're pulling away from the gate.

149
00:16:24,244 --> 00:16:26,974
...as a consultant to work
with crash survivors.

150
00:16:27,948 --> 00:16:32,112
One of my perks is free tickets.
Seatbelt, I think you should put it on.

151
00:16:33,087 --> 00:16:35,351
But I have to travel so much for work...

152
00:16:35,823 --> 00:16:37,723
...that my idea of a vacation...

153
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:40,993
That's normal.

154
00:16:41,061 --> 00:16:42,961
...is just to stay put.

155
00:16:43,230 --> 00:16:44,697
I'm not scared.

156
00:16:45,933 --> 00:16:47,798
But I would like another drink...

157
00:16:47,868 --> 00:16:49,335
...when we're airborne.

158
00:16:50,204 --> 00:16:51,933
I should say, if we're airborne.

159
00:17:13,660 --> 00:17:16,993
- Mom, he's here! He's really here!
- I knew you were all right.

160
00:17:20,768 --> 00:17:22,963
- I knew you were okay!
- We were so worried.

161
00:17:23,037 --> 00:17:24,095
It's a miracle.

162
00:17:27,241 --> 00:17:28,469
You're alive.

163
00:17:31,912 --> 00:17:33,379
I knew I couldn't lose you.

164
00:17:33,447 --> 00:17:35,415
- Coffee. Let's get coffee.
- Okay.

165
00:17:38,218 --> 00:17:41,847
- Look at you. He's perfect.
- Yes, he is. He's just fine.

166
00:17:43,490 --> 00:17:44,752
Come here.

167
00:17:47,728 --> 00:17:48,854
Were you scared?

168
00:17:49,963 --> 00:17:50,793
No.

169
00:17:51,065 --> 00:17:52,089
Not at all.

170
00:17:52,166 --> 00:17:53,155
Excuse me.

171
00:17:53,233 --> 00:17:56,293
- I'm Steven Brillstein.
- Nan asked if he could wait here.

172
00:17:56,470 --> 00:17:57,698
He's a lawyer.

173
00:17:57,771 --> 00:17:59,568
I'm sorry to intrude, but...

174
00:18:00,174 --> 00:18:04,110
...Mrs. Gordon's frustrated. The airline
can't make a definite identification.

175
00:18:04,178 --> 00:18:05,076
Jeff's dead.

176
00:18:05,145 --> 00:18:06,169
Oh, my God!

177
00:18:06,246 --> 00:18:07,235
Jesus, Max!

178
00:18:08,048 --> 00:18:10,039
Max isn't himself right now.

179
00:18:11,618 --> 00:18:13,210
How do you know? We just met.

180
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:16,756
- I'm Bill Perlman.
- He's a therapist, works for the airline.

181
00:18:17,624 --> 00:18:19,285
I'm here for you, Max.

182
00:18:19,359 --> 00:18:22,920
If the airline pays your bills,
then it's a conflict of interest.

183
00:18:23,263 --> 00:18:26,699
I have to warn Mr. Klein
that anything he says in your presence...

184
00:18:26,767 --> 00:18:28,394
Is in confidence. It's my agreement.

185
00:18:28,469 --> 00:18:30,130
Let's talk about that later.

186
00:18:32,272 --> 00:18:34,536
Nan doesn't know.
She thinks if you're alive...

187
00:18:34,608 --> 00:18:35,836
I'll tell her.

188
00:18:37,578 --> 00:18:38,977
Can we speak privately?

189
00:18:39,046 --> 00:18:40,707
This is inappropriate.

190
00:18:40,981 --> 00:18:42,881
All right, out. Get out!

191
00:18:43,317 --> 00:18:44,409
We should talk.

192
00:18:45,352 --> 00:18:46,444
Max, relax.

193
00:18:47,621 --> 00:18:49,282
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

194
00:18:50,057 --> 00:18:51,888
I didn't hit him very hard.

195
00:18:53,861 --> 00:18:55,590
I can't help you right now.

196
00:18:57,097 --> 00:18:59,122
If you need anything, call me.

197
00:19:03,637 --> 00:19:06,868
In fairness to Mrs. Gordon,
I should hear the details.

198
00:19:18,252 --> 00:19:19,719
May I speak bluntly?

199
00:19:19,786 --> 00:19:21,048
I'd prefer it.

200
00:19:21,121 --> 00:19:23,521
You said you saw Mr. Gordon's dead body.

201
00:19:28,896 --> 00:19:32,332
Let me give you a piece of advice.
When you speak to your lawyer...

202
00:19:32,533 --> 00:19:35,525
...emphasize that you saw
your partner's dead body...

203
00:19:36,436 --> 00:19:38,802
...and think hard about what else you saw.

204
00:19:38,872 --> 00:19:41,773
It doesn't matter what you've said
to anybody so far.

205
00:19:41,842 --> 00:19:44,310
With accidents there's a delayed reaction.

206
00:19:44,711 --> 00:19:47,544
Memories of what happened
return gradually.

207
00:19:47,614 --> 00:19:51,209
I know, I'm terrible to talk about it but...

208
00:19:52,219 --> 00:19:54,619
...it's important that you remember...

209
00:19:54,688 --> 00:19:58,488
...if you saw Mr. Gordon actually be killed.

210
00:20:00,260 --> 00:20:01,659
Another thing to remember:

211
00:20:01,728 --> 00:20:04,697
If he wasn't killed instantly...

212
00:20:04,798 --> 00:20:06,561
...if he was in any pain...

213
00:20:06,767 --> 00:20:09,463
You telling me how to lie
so I can get more money?

214
00:20:12,072 --> 00:20:14,700
To be honest with you,
I wasn't thinking about you.

215
00:20:14,775 --> 00:20:16,640
I was thinking about Mrs. Gordon.

216
00:20:16,777 --> 00:20:18,836
She's not from a rich family and...

217
00:20:18,979 --> 00:20:21,106
...now she's a widow with two children.

218
00:20:21,782 --> 00:20:23,010
What? What?

219
00:20:25,285 --> 00:20:26,513
What? What's wrong?

220
00:20:26,587 --> 00:20:28,680
I don't want to tell any lies.

221
00:20:29,289 --> 00:20:30,347
All right.

222
00:20:30,791 --> 00:20:32,383
Next time, just say no.

223
00:20:38,966 --> 00:20:40,661
Good evening, Mr. Klein.

224
00:20:41,969 --> 00:20:43,436
Don't scream, okay?

225
00:20:43,570 --> 00:20:47,529
Just bear in mind, you're sitting pretty,
you get the partnership insurance.

226
00:20:48,108 --> 00:20:50,542
I think you owe Mrs. Gordon anything...

227
00:20:50,677 --> 00:20:53,578
...that could improve her settlement
with the airlines.

228
00:21:03,757 --> 00:21:05,190
One other thing:

229
00:21:06,793 --> 00:21:09,591
I had all night to go through
Mr. Gordon's papers.

230
00:21:10,731 --> 00:21:13,427
He cashed in the tickets
that you ordered on AMEX.

231
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:15,900
Got a better price,
rebought them for cash...

232
00:21:15,969 --> 00:21:17,903
...and pocketed the difference.

233
00:21:19,439 --> 00:21:21,737
So Jeff cheated me out of $200.

234
00:21:21,875 --> 00:21:23,809
So he cheated his wife...

235
00:21:24,077 --> 00:21:27,205
...out of the automatic
American Express insurance.

236
00:21:28,081 --> 00:21:29,946
That's another reason why...

237
00:21:30,550 --> 00:21:34,884
...your memory of what happened
on the plane is so important.

238
00:21:58,211 --> 00:21:59,337
Steady.

239
00:22:00,314 --> 00:22:01,906
I knew it. I just knew it...

240
00:22:02,015 --> 00:22:03,209
...right away.

241
00:22:04,885 --> 00:22:06,182
- We were stupid.
- No, you weren't.

242
00:22:06,253 --> 00:22:07,720
We lived like jerks.

243
00:22:08,288 --> 00:22:11,155
Always nagging. We wasted it.

244
00:22:12,125 --> 00:22:13,524
He loved you.

245
00:22:16,730 --> 00:22:18,220
Mom, keep the kids...

246
00:22:21,535 --> 00:22:23,867
- Let's go back to your room.
- Why's she crying?

247
00:22:23,970 --> 00:22:25,528
You made him happy.

248
00:22:25,706 --> 00:22:26,900
He loved you.

249
00:22:28,542 --> 00:22:29,839
He loved you.

250
00:22:30,677 --> 00:22:32,144
Max, please shut up.

251
00:22:59,106 --> 00:23:00,505
Let me hold you.

252
00:23:04,778 --> 00:23:06,370
Why didn't you call?

253
00:23:06,613 --> 00:23:07,637
Where were you?

254
00:23:07,714 --> 00:23:09,375
I was visiting my past.

255
00:23:10,016 --> 00:23:12,280
But why didn't you tell me you were alive?

256
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:15,010
I thought I was dead.

257
00:23:32,539 --> 00:23:34,166
How does it feel to be a hero?

258
00:23:35,709 --> 00:23:37,904
How did it feel those last few seconds?

259
00:23:41,915 --> 00:23:43,143
It's me.

260
00:23:47,254 --> 00:23:48,915
We live in the same city.

261
00:23:48,989 --> 00:23:50,183
Isn't that great?

262
00:23:53,093 --> 00:23:54,924
This is my son, Jonah.

263
00:23:55,262 --> 00:23:56,251
Hi, I'm Byron.

264
00:23:56,329 --> 00:23:58,160
Did you know the plane would crash?

265
00:23:58,231 --> 00:23:59,664
I want to get on the bus.

266
